28 MODIFY PROVISIONS RELATED TO JUVENILE CUSTODY
29 SECTION 10.(a) G.S. 7B-1903 reads as rewritten:
30 "§ 7B-1903. Criteria for secure or nonsecure custody.
31 (a) When a request is made for nonsecure custody, the court shall first consider release
32 of the juvenile to the juvenile's parent, guardian, custodian, or other responsible adult. An order
33 for nonsecure custody shall be made only when there is a reasonable factual basis to believe the
