20 General Statutes, or proceedings for abuse, neglect, or exploitation of an adult under Article 6 or
21 6A of Chapter 108A of the General Statutes.
22 Nothing in this subsection shall be construed as permitting an individual to obtain immunity
23 from prosecution for criminal conduct or as excusing an individual from reporting requirements
24 of the General Statutes, including Article 3 of Chapter 7B of the General Statutes, Article 39 of
25 Chapter 14 of the General Statutes, G.S. 108A-102, or G.S. 110-105.4."
26 SECTION 18.(b) G.S. 7A-38.4A(j) reads as rewritten:
27 "(j) Evidence of statements made and conduct occurring in a mediated settlement
28 conference or other settlement proceeding conducted under this section, whether attributable to
29 a party, the mediator, other neutral, or a neutral observer present at the settlement proceeding,
30 shall not be subject to discovery and shall be inadmissible in any proceeding in the action or other
31 civil actions on the same claim, except:
32 (1) In proceedings for sanctions under this section;
33 (2) In proceedings to enforce or rescind a settlement of the action;
34 (3) In disciplinary proceedings before the State Bar or the Dispute Resolution
35 Commission; or
36 (4) In proceedings to enforce laws concerning juvenile or elder abuse.for abuse,
37 neglect, or dependency of a juvenile under Chapter 7B of the General Statutes,
38 or proceedings for abuse, neglect, or exploitation of an adult under Article 6
39 or 6A of Chapter 108A of the General Statutes.
40 As used in this subsection, the term "neutral observer" includes persons seeking mediator
41 certification, persons studying dispute resolution processes, and persons acting as interpreters.
42 No settlement agreement to resolve any or all issues reached at the proceeding conducted
43 under this section or during its recesses shall be enforceable unless it has been reduced to writing
44 and signed by the parties against whom enforcement is sought and in all other respects complies
45 with the requirements of Chapter 50 of the General Statutes. No evidence otherwise discoverable
46 shall be inadmissible merely because it is presented or discussed in a settlement proceeding.
47 No mediator, other neutral, or neutral observer present at a settlement proceeding under this
48 section, shall be compelled to testify or produce evidence concerning statements made and
49 conduct occurring in anticipation of, during, or as a follow-up to a mediated settlement
50 conference or other settlement proceeding pursuant to this section in any civil proceeding for any
51 purpose, including proceedings to enforce or rescind a settlement of the action, except to attest
